"n. 纪念品 【英】 n. 纪念品(souvenir) 【记】 mement(时刻)+o→记 住那一时刻→纪念品 n. 纪念品; 遗物(用以提醒过去的东西) 【记】源于: remember(v 回忆起) 【参】memorial(n 纪念物; 纪念碑) 【记】memory 记忆 + to 给某人，给某人做记忆的→纪念品 memento (n.)  c.1400, ""Psalm cxxxi in the Canon of the Mass"" (which begins with the Latin word Memento and in which the dead are commemorated), from Latin memento ""remember,"" imperative of meminisse ""to remember, recollect, think of, bear in mind,"" a reduplicated form, related to mens ""mind"" (see mind (n.)). Meaning ""reminder, object serving as a warning"" is from 1580s; sense of ""keepsake"" is first recorded 1768."
